ents into thinking their hits have landed. You gain the ability to make combat maneuvers, if you couldn&rsquo;t already. After an enemy misses an attack targeting you, by accepting a point of stress, you may roll a Performance skill check to pretend to be mortally wounded, immediately falling prone and convincing the enemies that you are dead. Enemies convinced that you are dead will be unlikely to attack you and will only discover you are alive if they inspect your &ldquo;corpse.&rdquo;</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #38761d; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Additionally, in a fight with an audience, you are adept at gaining favor, and may deal an additional d6 of damage when dealing attack damage to determination points.</span><br></span></p>","save":"","skill":"Performance","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675984103641,"modifiedTime":1675984559743,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"BdjDcE6MuXQIU3FA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
